Use the standard library
This is how to anti_shuffle of s:
   Remember that n is s's length
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Add result to item i in s
      Increase i
   End do
   Remember that start is 0
   Do this n times:
      When start is at least n, then:
         Leave the loop
      End when
      Remember that stop is start
      Do this n times:
         When stop is at least n, then:
            Leave the loop
         End when
         Remember that c is item stop in result
         When c is 32, then:
            Leave the loop
         End when
         Increase stop
      End do
      Remember that len is diff of stop and start
      Remember that a is start
      Do this len times:
         Remember that best is a
         Remember that j is sum of a and 1
         Remember that remain is diff of stop and j
         Do this remain times:
            When item j in result is less than item best in result, then:
               Remember that best is j
            End when
            Increase j
         End do
         When best is not a, then:
            Remember that tmp is item a in result
            Remember that item a in result is item best in result
            Remember that item best in result is tmp
         End when
         Increase a
      End do
      When stop is at least n, then:
         Remember that start is n
      But, if not:
         Remember that start is sum of stop and 1
      End when
   End do
   The answer is result
